# Build artifacts: regenerated by `go build`, never source of truth.
/server
*.exe

# Test/coverage output (e.g. `go test -coverprofile`): transient, machine-specific.
*.out

# Secrets and local config: must never reach the remote.
.env

# Personal Claude instructions: local working notes, not part of the shipped project.
CLAUDE.local.md

# Learning write-ups: kept local while drafting; not part of the service itself.
content

# Planning docs: internal scaffolding for the build, not shipped artifacts.
PROJECT1_BUILD_PLAN.md
PROJECT2_BUILD_PLAN.md

# Terraform: state can hold secrets and resource metadata (never commit it), and
# .terraform/ caches large provider binaries. The .terraform.lock.hcl lock file
# IS committed so provider versions stay reproducible.
**/.terraform/
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
*.tfvars
*.tfvars.json
crash.log
